text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia rendlei is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The dense, spreading and pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.1 metres (1.0 to 3.6 ft). It blooms from October to December and produces yellow flowers.
